---
description: Forms, validation, React Hook Form, and Zod rules
globs:
  - "src/**/*.ts"
  - "src/**/*.tsx"
---

Forms and validation rules:
- Use Zod for input schemas
- Reuse schemas instead of duplicating validation rules across client and server
- Use React Hook Form for non-trivial client forms
- Use @hookform/resolvers/zod when wiring RHF to Zod
- Keep server-side validation authoritative
- Prefer schema-driven form types inferred from Zod when practical

Implementation rules:
- Keep form components focused on rendering and user interaction
- Keep mutation logic in Server Actions or server utilities, not embedded deeply in UI components
- Return structured error states suitable for the UI
- Keep success/error messages concise and user-friendly

Do not:
- Scatter validation logic across unrelated files
- Trust client-only validation
- Mix form rendering, persistence, and unrelated business logic in one giant component